title.narrative: Western Indonesia National Roads Improvement Project

description.narrative: The Project Development Objective (PDO) is to increase the effective use of selected sections of national roads along the Western Sumatera Corridor by reducing road user costs and to restore the functionality of selected sections of national and sub-national roads in disaster-affected areas in Central Sulawesi.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.A | Description: The Borrower shall maintain until completion of the Project the PMU withstaffing, supported by CTC and DSC with TOR satisfactory to the Borrower and the Bank | Frequency: during the whole duration of theproject

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.B | Description: For each of WP-2 WP-3, the detailed designs, schedule, supervisionarrangements and budgets shall be prepared and discussed, revised as necessary and implemented satisfactorily | Frequency: 90 daysafter DGH has entered into the contract with the Design and Supervision consultants

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.B | Description: The Borrower shall implement the Project in accordance with the ProjectManagement Manual and the Project Implementation Plan | Frequency: during the whole duration of the project

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section I.C | Description: Each subproject and linked subproject shall be carried out in accordancewith the provisions of ESMF and LARAP. The Borrower shall report the status of compliance as part of Project Reports | Frequency:during the whole duration of the project

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2, Section IV.B | Description: For category 4 of the project, no withdrawal shall be made until: (i)the Borrower has declared a disaster, emergency or catastrophic event and (ii) the Bank and the Borrower have entered into awritten arrangement | Frequency: Yearly
Finance Agreement: Section 4.01 | Description: Bid documents of WP-1, PMM, PIP and PMU satisfactory to the Bank | Due Date:14-Mar-2012
